So I have three children who went through the consolidated school system, and if they learned one thing, it was how to manipulate people because of their exposure to so many people.
They had students in and out at all times.
So I think that that is a hazard of our young people who will be in this community or at Huntsville or Austin
or certainly the Houston area where as we have to send our young people out for observation more and more.
So I see that as a real problem.
It's going to be difficult for us from one point of view, but our student teaching centers are
in what we call the best areas of the state, regardless of the close proximity to the university.
For example, we go to Fredericksburg, Mason, Bracken Ridge, all the way to the Oklahoma border, Sherman.
We go to the Houston schools.
We go south of San Antonio to Jurgenton.
To place your students for student teaching?
For student teaching.
So even that may have to change on us.
Do you still have to follow the whole semester that the College of Education requires?
We do not follow the whole semester.
We are six weeks on campus and nine weeks off campus in student teaching.
I really appreciate your time and your perception.
Well, good luck to you.
Thank you.
